Multimodal Ant simulation server

This repository contains a VersatIL socket-server wrapper for the multimodal
Ant maze task.

Upstream components:
- `ant_sim/ant_maze_multimodal.py` and `ant_sim/assets/` are adapted from
  jayLEE0301/vq_bet_official/envs/antenv (MIT license, Copyright (c) 2024
  Seungjae Lee), ported from gym/mujoco_py to gymnasium and the modern
  mujoco bindings. The adaptation also seeds the initial torso position from
  the per-environment random state instead of the global numpy state.
- The VQ-BeT ant environment itself builds on the ant maze environments from
  google-research (efficient-hrl / HIRO lineage).

The repository-level Apache-2.0 license applies to VersatIL wrapper/adaptation
code contributed here. Vendored simulator files retain their original
upstream terms unless a file-level license states otherwise.
